<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-553-585  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 553 585.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Oct 29 1990 v7 n44 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users question FCC praise of price caps. (Federal CommunicationsCommission)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A Federal Communications Commission (FCC) report is praising thefirst year of ATandamp;T's price cap regulation but trade associationsand user groups contend that the report only promotes FCC policiesand does not seriously study price cap performance.andP;  The FCCreport claims the price cap plan is a success due to $727 millionin rate reductions, an absence of increased market dominance orover-earning and the maintenance of network quality.andP;  Criticspoint out that the report lacks a comparison of the results of theprice cap plan with projections of what would have resulted underrate-of-return regulation.andP;  They are also questioning the way datais presented in the report and why recent figures are notincluded.andP;  The report states that price cap regulation has notcaused ATandamp;T to cut back on network upgrades and maintenance inorder to cut costs and increase profits.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Services).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionPricing PolicyReportsCritique.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   ATandamp;T's price cap performance. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>